{
  "stem": "26142.9",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When I told her that I have two brothers, the one is here and the other one is with his wife and two children, that they were going to register in the Judenrat because they can get a meal there, she says, oh no, don't do that.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Don't.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You tell your brother not to go there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I said, well, why not?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She says, I'll tell you why.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because the Germans come in every day, and they take people out for the dirtiest work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They demanded from the Judenrat to give them so many hands.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And what the Judenrat usually does-- she was very open with it-- they usually, instead of sending local people, local Jews-- they send the Hungarian refugees.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Of course, we notified our brother not to do it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she says, don't worry about that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Little soup that you were going to get, whatever we will eat, you will eat with this.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it was really very, very-- [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] how should I say that?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Very nice of her that-- what she did.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She gave us the right answer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Now we are 50 kilometers from home. 50 kilometers usually could be walked in about eight hours, 10 hours the most.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But all of a sudden, we started hearing rumors coming in from people that went to the border and the border police caught them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they took them in back to Hungary and then they loaded them up and shipped them out to Stanislawow, and you never heard from-- and in the meantime, some of the Hungarian border guards, they learned that this is a good opportunity to rob people.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they kill the people because they figured maybe they have maybe some jewelery, maybe some money.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
